      "span_text": "It is possible to see that a Gypsy-Traveller site could sit within this definition to a degree, being spatially concentrated (often on the margins, but sometimes tucked away in central industrial parts of the city) and those living on the site being involuntarily defined as 'other' and often judged as inferior. The balance of power in relation to Gypsy-Traveller sites is very heavily in favour of the dominant society, outside the site; but there are degrees of power and control being exercised within too. [CITATION_1] highlights the challenges inherent in attempting to transplant the notion of the 'ghetto' into other urban realities where they do not directly translate."
